 Kong, Macau and Taiwan. Now for the first time, these reports are available in English for anyone interested in Chinese language and linguistics, China's language, education and social policies, as well as everyday language use among the ordinary people in China. The invaluable data contained in these reports provide an essential reference to researchers, professionals, policy makers, and China watchers.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBilingualismxChina. 0aBilingualismzChina. 0aChinese languagexVariation. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxChina. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzChina. 0aLanguage and culturexChina. 0aLanguage and culturezChina. 0aLanguage and educationxChina. 0aLanguage and educationzChina. 0aLanguage planningxChina. 0aLanguage planningzChina. 0aLanguage policyxChina. 0aLanguage policyzChina. 4aChinesisch. 4aChinesische Sprache. 4aLinguistik. 4aSprachplanung. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aChina.  aChinese Language.  aLanguage Policy and Planning.  aLanguage Variety.1 aAhata, Shayelan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAqing, Hao, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBingbing, Jiang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuiye, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDan, Wei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaojuan, Zhou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDingqian, Gu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErhong, Yang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeng, Luo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo